cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a novel loss function for deep neural network architectures in image classification and human pose estimation tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the difficulty of disambiguating visually similar objects and symmetric body parts, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed loss function involves dynamically rescaling the cross entropy based on prediction difficulty, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed loss function on two different domains, which could also suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
